  "meta": {
    "schema_version": "4.0",
    "created_at": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z",
    "notes": "SKEWED STRADDLE — BULL BIAS. Structure: 1 lot CE sell + 2 lot PE sell. WHY: On a mildly bullish day, PE decays much faster as market drifts up. The extra PE lot amplifies this theta advantage. Net credit is higher than a symmetric strangle. RISK: If market falls hard, 2x PE lots means 2x losses on that side — worse than DNSS. That is why the PANIC rule fires at 0.60 delta to roll before losses compound. ADJUSTMENT LADDER: (1) Panic at delta 0.60 → roll PE 2 lots to fresh 0.25 delta. (2) View confirmed (spot up 0.6% + CE profit 40%) → close CE leg, ride PE decay alone. (3) View wrong (spot down 0.7% + delta skew) → reduce PE from 2 to 1 lot (symmetric). (4) Flat day + small delta → rebalance. ENTRY GATE: PCR > 1.0 (market leans bullish) + spot not already down. TO CREATE BEAR VERSION: swap CE and PE everywhere — sell 2 CE + 1 PE, PCR condition < 1.0, spot_change_pct condition reversed."
  },
